---
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav/index.astro';
import SkipToContent from '../components/SkipToContent/index.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Base/index.astro';

const BLOG_URL = Astro.site?.href;
---
<BaseLayout
	htmlTitle={['Offline', 'TorontoJS Blog']}
	title="Offline Page"
	url={`${BLOG_URL}offline`}
	description="Offline page for the TorontoJS blog. If you are offline, you can still navigate the site, but some content might not be available."
	tags={['development', 'javascript', 'toronto', 'community', 'blog']}
>
	<SkipToContent slot="header" />
	<header slot="header">
		<SiteNav />
		<h1>404 - Not found</h1>
	</header>

	<div id="contents">
		<p>Looks like you hit a dead-end. It seems though the site is downloaded <em>or</em> you are offline.</p>

		<p>All pages are still navegable and you should have <strong>no problems</strong> visiting most pages.</p>
		<p>If you are completely offline, you won't be able to see or use:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Images from pages not visited before.</li>
			<li>Some dynamic content, like adding comments.</li>
		</ul>

		<p>
			<a href={BLOG_URL}>Go back to the blog home</a>
		</p>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
